http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 18 Sep 2021
Source: OIE-WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2021 [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=39905


African swine fever [ASF], Haiti
-----------------------------------
General information
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 26 Aug 2021
Confirmed: 17 Sep 2021
Reported: 18 Sep 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 20 Sep 1984
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

Outbreak location: City of Anse-a-Pitre, Anse-a-Pitre, Belle-Anse, Sud-Est
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Aug 2021
Epidemiological unit: backyard
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Swine / 2500 / 1 / 234 / 3 / 750 / 0

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Control measures at event level
Domestic control measures applied: quarantine, surveillance outside containment and/or the protection zone, screening

Domestic control measures to be applied: zoning; surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone; selective killing and disposal; movement control inside the country; ante- and post-mortem inspections; disinfection; disinfestation; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; official destruction of animal products

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Outbreaks / Test / Test date / Result
Foreign Animal Disease Diagnostic Laboratory (FADDL), Plum Island Animal Disease Center (OIE reference laboratory) / swine / 1 / real-time polymerase chain reaction (real-time PCR) / 17 Sep 2021 / positive

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URLs above.]

