Communicated by:
ProMED
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The last occurrence of ASF in Haiti was in 1984. Unfortunately, due to the situation of ASF in the Dominican Republic, it's not surprising that ASF is now reported in Haiti. The outbreak is located near the border with Dominican Republic.

"Anse-a-Pitres is a commune in the Southeast Department of Haiti. Part of the Belle-Anse Arrondissement, it lies on the coast of the Caribbean Sea, approximately 140 km (85 miles) south of Port-au-Prince, immediately adjacent to the border with Dominican Republic. The town occupies the southeasternmost corner of Haiti."
https://haiti.fandom.com/wiki/Anse-%C3%A0-Pitres

A map of Haiti showing regional divisions is available at https://www.nationsonline.org/maps/haiti_map.jpg.

Readers will be interested to review a series of webinars that the US Department of Agriculture's Animal and Plant Health Inspection Service hosted 13-17 Sep 2021. The webinars describe the occurrence of African swine fever virus, its global spread, actions APHIS is taking to safeguard the United States, and biosecurity measures that can be implemented to protect the US herd. The recorded webinars are available at https://www.aphis.usda.gov/aphis/ourfocus/animalhealth/animal-disease-information/swine-disease-information/african-swine-fever/seminar/asf-action-week. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED map of Anse-a-Pitre, Sud-Est, Haiti: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8689382,48874]
